            <title>[CASSANDRA-3451] estimated row sizes regression</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3451</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2753&quot; title=&quot;Capture the max client timestamp for an SSTable&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-2753&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-2753&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; broke the histogram collection; it got the histogram for column count (which can go up to 2B) switched with the one for row size in bytes (which goes up to ~1.5PB).  So any row over 2GB, will break things.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
